{"key":"processedPost-9122757","value":{"id":9122757,"first":9121864,"last":9134480,"when":1224807805,"utime":"10/24/08 03:23 AM","content":"Here's the deal.<br />Mechanical hygrometers have a hair, often a human hair that expands and contracts due to humidity.&nbsp; Any of you members with long hair knows this happens.&nbsp; This hair pulls against a spring which is attached to the dial.&nbsp; It's a simple instrument, but is only accurate through a narrow band, because a hair will only expand and contract so much, regardless of the change in humidity.<br />If you're using the hygrometer in your house, or in a cigar humidor, use the salt method, since that is the range you want it to be accurate in.<br />If you're using the hygrometer in a fruiting chamber, use the damp towel method, since you want your accuracy in the 95% range.<br />RR","title":"Re: Another issue with humidity"}}